  <div id="tribute-info">
    <p>Dr. Norman Borlaug was an American biologist, humanitarian, and Nobel laureate who has been called "the father of the Green Revolution," "agriculture's greatest spokesperson," and "The Man Who Saved A Billion Lives".</p>
    <p>Borlaug was one of only six people to have won the Nobel Peace Prize, the Presidential Medal of Freedom, and the Congressional Gold Medal. He was also a member of the National Academy of Sciences and the recipient of numerous other honors and awards.</p>
  </div>
